-- Microsoft Says U.S. Stores Sold 261,000 Xbox Players in March
-- B y   C l i f f   E d w a r d s
-- 2013-04-18T22:16:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-18/microsoft-says-u-s-stores-sold-261-000-xbox-players-in-march.html
Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  said U.S. retailers
sold 261,000 Xbox 360 game consoles last month, holding its spot
as the No. 1 selling model in March.  Spending on Xbox 360 hardware, software and accessories
totaled $402 million last month, Redmond, Washington-based
Microsoft said today in an e-mailed statement, citing data from
researcher NPD group Inc.  NPD, based in Port Washington, New York, is scheduled to
report video-game sales for the month and year to date later
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cliff Edwards in  San Francisco  at 
